-- Lehman close to raising more than $5 bln: paper
-- 
-- Sun Jun 8, 2008 7:41pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/08/us-lehmanbrothers-idUSWEN611020080608

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc is close to raising more than $5 billion and is set to report a loss of more than $2 billion in the second quarter, The Wall Street Journal reported on its Web site on Sunday. 

 The fresh capital would come from investors including the New Jersey Division of Investment, the paper reported, citing an unnamed source. The final details of the capital raise were being worked out and could be announced Monday or Tuesday, the paper said. (Reporting by  Paritosh Bansal , editing by Martin Golan)